ncern-that-may-grow-its-own-m-ac7ebe2c40", :entity/name "The propose-revision command that constructs `:essay-revise` actions from buffer state. That command is needed and will land as part of Stage 1's command set, but its predict-effects-rendering UX is a sibling concern that may grow its own m", :entity/type :bounded-item, :entity/props {:scope/role "bounded-item", :mission "M-editorial-assistant"}, :xt/id "scope/bounded-item/the-propose-revision-command-that-constructs-essay-revise-actions-from-buffer-state-that-command-is-needed-and-will-land-as-part-of-stage-1-s-command-set-but-its-predict-effects-rendering-ux-is-a-sibling-concern-that-may-grow-its-own-m-ac7ebe2c40"} {:entity/id "00005e2c-cf8c-46ae-b1c2-ba8c4c4b2842", :entity/name "futon-theory/counter-ratchet/03-invariant-statement", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "INVARIANT-STATEMENT", :entity/source "explicitly acknowledged deletion occurs.\n    I2 (extended): Key counts are monotonically non-decreasing unless", :xt/id "00005e2c-cf8c-46ae-b1c2-ba8c4c4b2842"} {:entity/id "00011043-4080-4d10-b350-9c1fc2e14cf3", :entity/name "futon-theory/error-hierarchy/02-context", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "context", :entity/source "surfaces first.\n    hunting in the wrong codebase. Layer hierarchy ensures the true cause\n    instead of minutes. An auth error that masks a storage failure sends you\nWhen errors surface at the wrong layer, debugging takes hours", :xt/id "00011043-4080-4d10-b350-9c1fc2e14cf3"} {:entity/id "000169fc-f758-4b98-8dd7-dfe68e04fd0a", :entity/name "futon-theory/mission-dependency/because", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "futon-theory/mission-dependency/because", :entity/source "- Explicit dependencies prevent wasted work on blocked missions\n    - Graph structure enables priority inference\n    - Unblock propagation accelerates overall progress\n    - Shared resources surface coordination needs", :xt/id "000169fc-f758-4b98-8dd7-dfe68e04fd0a"} {:entity/id "000c9481-ddbf-4e30-aa52-79a3bea96e84", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-024/if", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "iiching/exotype-024/if", :entity/source "You need an explicit, searchable exotype record.", :xt/id "000c9481-ddbf-4e30-aa52-79a3bea96e84"} {:entity/id "000e6c80-3650-449c-b59c-e779e8c0fd8c", :entity/name "math-strategy/characterization-result/next-steps", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "math-strategy/characterization-result/next-steps", :entity/source "next[Decide whether the characterization is full, partial / failure-mode, classification, or dichotomy.]\n      next[Identify the witness — list, theorem, equivalence — that constitutes the description.]\n      next[Cross-check: does the paper *prove the characterization is exhaustive*, or only *exhibit examples*?]", :xt/id "000e6c80-3650-449c-b59c-e779e8c0fd8c"} {:entity/id "0012f799-2294-4aef-8684-7d59bac5624f", :entity/name "p4ng/feedback-rhythms/06-because", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "because", :entity/source "Regular rhythms of feedback keep evolving systems aligned with changing conditions.", :xt/id "0012f799-2294-4aef-8684-7d59bac5624f"} {:entity/id "0019f409-3c0f-49b6-abee-ad4cbd96a573", :entity/name "ukrns/coding-provenance/because", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "ukrns/coding-provenance/because", :entity/source "Qualitative-to-numerical is load-bearing: the upgrade from textual NPT codes to [0, 1] values is the single most important epistemic step in the paper's empirical chain.  All downstream computation rests on it.  Provenance is the audit trail for that step.\n\n    Reviewer challenge defence: when a reviewer asks 'how do you know that FG2A-P1 has communal-specification 0.20?', the minimum adequate answer names the transcript passages, the coder, and the protocol.  Without provenance, the answer is 'someone coded it' — which is not a defence.\n\n    Coder-in-the-loop: provenance preserves coder identity and judgements.  This serves two purposes: accountability (coders stand behind their work) and governance (future coders can trace how earlier judgements were made, which informs calibration).\n\n    Commons-adjacent: the provenance record is itself a commons artefact.  Its governance (who can add, who can audit, how retention works) mirrors ukrns/assumptions-commons.\n\n    Projection into main patterns: without coding provenance, ukrns/diagnose-before-prescribing's profile signatures cannot be contested by institutions.  A profile's classification depends on its NPT scores; an institution challenging its classification needs access to the provenance to mount a defence.\n\n    Mechanic, in short:\n    Mechanic: how the qualitative-to-numerical upgrade is traced.\n    Serves: computation-as-exploration's inspectability claim at the upstream end.\n    Axis: full traceability ↔ aggregate provenance.\n    Without this pattern: the empirical base is oracle, the upgrade is private, and the paper's computational claims rest on unauditable judgements.", :xt/id "0019f409-3c0f-49b6-abee-ad4cbd96a573"} {:entity/id "001bb18a-2dda-4af4-9c4d-07322c31f3b1", :entity/name "sidecar/sense-shift-gate/because", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "sidecar/sense-shift-gate/because", :entity/source "Gating reduces drift and keeps chains explainable.", :xt/id "001bb18a-2dda-4af4-9c4d-07322c31f3b1"} {:entity/id "0023d8e6-ba06-4882-a80e-a6616634afe6", :entity/name "equity/contribution-pathways/08-invariant-statement", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "INVARIANT-STATEMENT", :entity/source "Every participant who sustains engagement beyond initial training has at least one visible route to contribute to programme development, governance, or community support. Sustained contribution creates recognised standing in the programme's governance structure.", :xt/id "0023d8e6-ba06-4882-a80e-a6616634afe6"} {:entity/id "00295e22-bf18-45d6-bf66-be0078055dde", :entity/name "futon5a-d/excursion/trip-journal-hit", :entity/type :excursion/doc, :entity/external-id "E-trip-journal-hit", :entity/source "excursion-doc-backfill", :entity/props {:excursion/id "trip-journal-hit", :excursion/title "E-trip-journal-hit", :excursion/status "unknown", :excursion/parent-mission nil}, :xt/id "00295e22-bf18-45d6-bf66-be0078055dde"} {:entity/id "002a0a8c-c83b-4e0b-b598-b17317058052", :entity/name "pattern-coherence/causal-clarity/however", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "pattern-coherence/causal-clarity/however", :entity/source "Some domains rely on tacit practice and the mechanism may be partially inferred.", :xt/id "002a0a8c-c83b-4e0b-b598-b17317058052"} {:entity/id "002d3b86-c679-4455-a502-0b388b0b6110", :entity/name "liberation/noble/right-action/if", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "liberation/noble/right-action/if", :entity/source "Even skilled refraining involves an actor — one who takes credit for not harming, who is proud of not taking. The restraint can become another form of self-construction.", :xt/id "002d3b86-c679-4455-a502-0b388b0b6110"} {:entity/id "002fbb45-896f-47da-ac5a-58f64ed75623", :entity/name "pattern-coherence/causal-clarity/04-however", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "HOWEVER", :entity/source "Some domains rely on tacit practice and the mechanism may be partially inferred.", :xt/id "002fbb45-896f-47da-ac5a-58f64ed75623"} {:entity/id "0030a6e9-f433-42e9-8c3f-00ca295a29d2", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-157", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "iiching/exotype-157", :entity/source "Exotype 157 (0x9D)", :xt/id "0030a6e9-f433-42e9-8c3f-00ca295a29d2"} {:entity/id "003193d6-0e2c-4a65-8a14-14985709c452", :entity/name "ukrns/open-the-triangle/09-because", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "BECAUSE", :entity/source "Network learning requires a shared layer: The paper's central move is from isolated training activity toward a coordinated learning system.  That move fails if evidence never leaves the place where it was produced.\n\n    Wider recognition depends on shareable evidence: Funders and policy actors cannot act on local success they cannot see.  A service that wants sector-level standing needs forms of evidence that travel beyond the originating institution.\n\n    Persistence matters as much as publication: A one-off shared output is not yet infrastructure.  The pattern is about creating deposits that later cycles can inherit, revise, and build on.\n\n    Governance is part of the work, not an afterthought: The question is not whether evidence should be shared in the abstract, but which evidence is worth sharing at which governance cost.  Making that trade explicit is what keeps the pattern from becoming either secrecy by default or openness as a slogan.\n\n    Mechanic, in short:\n    Derived from the paper's need to connect local delivery, usable evidence, and sector recognition into one operating story.\n    Answers the service-level version of the visible-impact and shared-maintenance problems: what one institution learns should become part of the network's usable memory.\n    Mapped to the learning loop at the deposit step: evidence produced locally enters a shared layer so later actors can build on it.\n    Coordination requirement: Low for routine artefacts, high for cross-institution evaluation and anything carrying reputational consequence.", :xt/id "003193d6-0e2c-4a65-8a14-14985709c452"} {:entity/id "0037c244-e418-4edf-91f4-daa35fa592b7", :entity/name "p4ng/bridge-before-portal", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "p4ng/bridge-before-portal", :entity/source "Bridge-Before-Portal", :xt/id "0037c244-e418-4edf-91f4-daa35fa592b7"} {:entity/id "0038c790-863a-4bea-8f77-cded807a7dfe", :entity/name "futon-theory/baldwin-cycle/then", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "futon-theory/baldwin-cycle/then", :entity/source "Operate an explicit move on the named axis (see substructure below); steward the pattern against the declared discipline.", :xt/id "0038c790-863a-4bea-8f77-cded807a7dfe"} {:entity/id "003cac6a-bdbe-4a4a-8d4b-f415eb8461ff", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-162/however", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "iiching/exotype-162/however", :entity/source "The lift registry has no mapping for this exotype yet.", :xt/id "003cac6a-bdbe-4a4a-8d4b-f415eb8461ff"} {:entity/id "00418911-9f84-436a-a1bd-e4ebf1721b1e", :entity/name "exotic/dual-track-generation", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "exotic/dual-track-generation", :entity/source "Dual-Track Generated Patterns", :xt/id "00418911-9f84-436a-a1bd-e4ebf1721b1e"} {:entity/id "0048f61d-fffc-451d-ada1-8865aa956e69", :entity/name "futon-theory/theory-as-exotype/then", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "futon-theory/theory-as-exotype/then", :entity/source "Operate an explicit move on the named axis (see substructure below); steward the pattern against the declared discipline.", :xt/id "0048f61d-fffc-451d-ada1-8865aa956e69"} {:entity/id "0048fc56-49d7-4f7a-b19b-0606f0c162ed", :entity/name "ai4ci/process-vs-exposition/05-then", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "THEN", :entity/source "or expository—links to specific objects, steps, or subgoals in the proof.\n    anchor formal steps, and annotate how each informal phrase—whether exploratory\n    Analyse both kinds of cues: use baseline entity and relation extraction to", :xt/id "0048fc56-49d7-4f7a-b19b-0606f0c162ed"} {:entity/id "004a60d9-4940-4ed1-9a61-a33e765f0534", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-046/03-if", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "IF", :entity/source "You need an explicit, searchable exotype record.", :xt/id "004a60d9-4940-4ed1-9a61-a33e765f0534"} {:entity/id "004d9d71-c1a6-4400-a493-eebba085d543", :entity/name "sorry|devmap|futon4|P7|literary-interface", :entity/type :sorry, :entity/external-id "sorry|sorry|devmap|futon4|P7|literary-interface", :entity/source "stack-geometry-sorries", :entity/props {:sorry/next-steps ["Design manuscript mode UI" "Implement chapter/section chunking" "Add cross-reference map visualization" "Test with real manuscript content"], :sorry/however "No good UI for long-form text exists yet", :sorry/if "You want to edit books or long-form text via Arxana", :sorry/title "Prototype 7 — Literary Interface", :sorry/evidence-operational ["Arxana handles document fragments" "Scholium mode provides linking infrastructure"], :sorry/pass-criteria ["Long documents chunked into navigable sections" "Cross-references visualized and navigable" "Manuscript mode supports book-length content"], :sorry/maturity "greenfield", :sorry/inhabited-ness "unnamed", :sorry/sigils ["🙅/也" "💖/久"], :sorry/context "A literary interface supports long-form writing like books and manuscripts.", :sorry/scale "devmap", :sorry/depends-on-raw ["f4/P2"], :sorry/source {:file "/home/joe/code/futon3/holes/futon4.devmap", :order 7}, :sorry/status "open", :sorry/then "Add manuscript mode with chunking and cross-reference map", :sorry/id "sorry|devmap|futon4|P7|literary-interface", :sorry/fail-criteria ["Long documents unwieldy to edit"], :sorry/because "FUTON becomes a writing environment, not just an editor", :sorry/repo "futon4"}, :xt/id "004d9d71-c1a6-4400-a493-eebba085d543"} {:entity/id "0050b056-b8fd-4400-a6b3-9a44b8629fc6", :entity/name "vsatlas/accountable-poc/03-if", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "IF", :entity/source "Funders care whether minimal linking increases organisational value in the proof-of-concept phase.", :xt/id "0050b056-b8fd-4400-a6b3-9a44b8629fc6"} {:entity/id "005d6534-a25a-4f01-9b5d-d26e5b3645a8", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-227/context", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "iiching/exotype-227/context", :entity/source "Canonical 8-bit encoding for exotype 227.", :xt/id "005d6534-a25a-4f01-9b5d-d26e5b3645a8"} {:entity/id "00621227-dc