nhabited-ness "spec-only", :sorry/scale "excursion-sorry", :sorry/depends-on-raw ["sorry|excursion|E-candidate-queue|move-2"], :sorry/source {:file "/home/joe/code/futon0/analysis/excursions/E-candidate-queue-upsampling.md", :section "Moves"}, :sorry/status "open", :sorry/then "Pick EDN file / API endpoint / mission-control hand-off; include provenance (snapshot timestamp, query parameters)", :sorry/id "sorry|excursion|E-candidate-queue|move-3", :sorry/because "Without an export path, Moves 1 and 2 produce artefacts that don't flow", :sorry/repo "candidate-queue-move-3"}, :xt/id "0076d81c-d0c4-4f20-8f49-69ecd52d3cbf"} {:entity/id "0078ec0c-1208-48ff-8810-8e0e0a1d32f4", :entity/name "p4ng/maintainer-care", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "p4ng/maintainer-care", :entity/source "Maintainer Care", :xt/id "0078ec0c-1208-48ff-8810-8e0e0a1d32f4"} {:entity/id "00792cf5-b3a8-434d-9d02-506cb05755b5", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-026/05-then", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "THEN", :entity/source "and the lift registry for pattern evidence.\n    Use the encoding fields for identification, the manifest for program/params,", :xt/id "00792cf5-b3a8-434d-9d02-506cb05755b5"} {:entity/id "007bda05-35a9-4fb0-b763-9ab437baf588", :entity/name "dsc/traversal-first-chaptering/07-next-steps", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "NEXT-STEPS", :entity/source "next[Decide placement by where the work was done, not by where it would rhetorically strengthen an argument.]\n    next[Allow partial overlap between chapters; coherence emerges from cross-reference, not exclusion.]\n    next[Treat each FUTON chapter as answering: \"What terrain was explored here, and what was learned by operating within it?\"]", :xt/id "007bda05-35a9-4fb0-b763-9ab437baf588"} {:entity/id "007d819a-041c-4874-90d1-64674abe6a21", :entity/name "library-coherence/library-readme-sync/because", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "library-coherence/library-readme-sync/because", :entity/source "the canon exists to keep the public story honest—without README coverage, pattern maturity is impossible to audit", :xt/id "007d819a-041c-4874-90d1-64674abe6a21"} {:entity/id "008087ee-0eef-48e7-8513-b548b89328a7", :entity/name "liberation/mundane/right-mindfulness/then", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "liberation/mundane/right-mindfulness/then", :entity/source "Practice the four foundations: (1) mindfulness of body (breathing, postures, activities, parts, elements, decay), (2) mindfulness of feelings (pleasant, unpleasant, neutral), (3) mindfulness of mind (contracted/expanded, concentrated/scattered, liberated/not), (4) mindfulness of phenomena (hindrances, aggregates, sense bases, awakening factors, truths).", :xt/id "008087ee-0eef-48e7-8513-b548b89328a7"} {:entity/id "008220bb-a9de-4507-864a-b02bdf599c42", :entity/name "ants/cargo-return-discipline/03-if", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "IF", :entity/source "or stalls near the nest.\n    The agent has cargo ≥ 0.05, repeatedly chooses :return while `:dep` = 0,", :xt/id "008220bb-a9de-4507-864a-b02bdf599c42"} {:entity/id "0085ed1f-81a9-42ec-a446-1e2ce87a9178", :entity/name "ai4ci/sota-distinction", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "ai4ci/sota-distinction", :entity/source "Distinguishing This Project from Current Mathematical AI SOTA", :xt/id "0085ed1f-81a9-42ec-a446-1e2ce87a9178"} {:entity/id "008ec7e6-ef93-4682-83c3-d05cc6a810fd", :entity/name "realtime/liveness-heartbeats/07-next-steps", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "NEXT-STEPS", :entity/source "- evidence-shape: {:session/id :string, :transport :keyword, :last-received-seq :int, :last-sent-seq :int, :mode :keyword, :heartbeat/seconds :int, :missed/count :int, :missed/threshold :int, :stale/seconds :int, :grace/seconds :int, :stall/flagged? :boolean, :stall/reason :keyword, :stall/ts :string, :ts :string}\n    - evidence: measure time-to-stall detection vs real outage.\n    - evidence: correlate stalls with actual bridge failures.\n    - evidence: record false positives/negatives.\n    - evidence: tune heartbeat period vs noise and false alarms.", :xt/id "008ec7e6-ef93-4682-83c3-d05cc6a810fd"} {:entity/id "00904f3a-48ad-4b91-b4f0-8ca67be65a18", :entity/name "writing-coherence/triad-inflation/then", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "writing-coherence/triad-inflation/then", :entity/source "Operate an explicit move on the named axis (see substructure below); steward the pattern against the declared discipline.", :xt/id "00904f3a-48ad-4b91-b4f0-8ca67be65a18"} {:entity/id "0090ab43-5f8e-45df-bf78-1a0006267842", :entity/name "or2/spread-effort-assurance/07-next-steps", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "NEXT-STEPS", :entity/source "next[Add a simple tag or property to mark multi-day work and surface it in agenda checks.]", :xt/id "0090ab43-5f8e-45df-bf78-1a0006267842"} {:entity/id "00916c79-0620-49da-81ad-bc1fa01df426", :entity/name "pacspine/bonus-layer/next-steps", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "pacspine/bonus-layer/next-steps", :entity/source "next[Choose a rotating bench of bonus benefits; track which ones resonate.]", :xt/id "00916c79-0620-49da-81ad-bc1fa01df426"} {:entity/id "009b0b29-d5da-425a-829e-62523d8d49c1", :entity/name "ukrns/self-application/if", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "ukrns/self-application/if", :entity/source "The pattern operates on the axis: static artefact (frozen document, snapshot of claims) ↔ instantiating artefact (re-computable, argument emitted from evidence on each run).\n    Irreducible: a single artefact cannot be maximally static (frozen, universally readable, dependency-free) AND maximally instantiating (re-computable from live data, reflecting evidence-state-of-today).  These are different kinds of object.", :xt/id "009b0b29-d5da-425a-829e-62523d8d49c1"} {:entity/id "009da43b-0a3b-421e-9260-5c95c65b202e", :entity/name "plos-npt-with-small-n/scope-shield-via-companion-paper/07-compositions", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "COMPOSITIONS", :entity/source "(1) Scope-and-handoff statement.\n          Schema: {:this-paper <slice> :reserved <remainder> :companion <citation or \"forthcoming\"> :seam <construct | phase | method>}\n          Effect: makes the narrowing legible as design.\n      (2) Standalone-contribution claim.\n          Schema: {:contribution-of-this-slice <what it alone establishes>}\n          Effect: shows the piece is not a fragment dependent on the companion.\n      (3) Seam-justification.\n          Schema: {:why-this-seam <principled boundary> :not \"the same analysis halved\"}\n          Effect: distinguishes deliberate scoping from salami-slicing.", :xt/id "009da43b-0a3b-421e-9260-5c95c65b202e"} {:entity/id "009ebd0e-f14f-4e6e-a0a6-d56966c91e38", :entity/name "portal/first-class-query-interface", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "portal/first-class-query-interface", :entity/source "First-Class Query Interface", :xt/id "009ebd0e-f14f-4e6e-a0a6-d56966c91e38"} {:entity/id "00a0c5fb-056d-4750-89bd-1116923df09b", :entity/name "peeragogy/reciprocal-participation/if", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "peeragogy/reciprocal-participation/if", :entity/source "The pattern operates on the axis: producing-the-output ↔ giving-back-to-sources.\n    Irreducible: the people whose voices the practice carries cannot fully guard their own reciprocity if the practice itself doesn't make it a constraint.  The convener has more agency in the relationship than the contributor; the discipline puts that asymmetry on the table rather than papering over it with rhetoric.", :xt/id "00a0c5fb-056d-4750-89bd-1116923df09b"} {:entity/id "00a2b303-2976-404c-98d0-f481e94351bd", :entity/name "sidecar/explicit-promotion-to-facts", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "sidecar/explicit-promotion-to-facts", :entity/source "Explicit Promotion to Facts", :xt/id "00a2b303-2976-404c-98d0-f481e94351bd"} {:entity/id "00a8dd5d-9cf9-42c0-815c-bdd0037e708d", :entity/name "sidecar/append-only-semantic-audit", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "sidecar/append-only-semantic-audit", :entity/source "Append-Only Semantic Audit", :xt/id "00a8dd5d-9cf9-42c0-815c-bdd0037e708d"} {:entity/id "00abf421-55a2-4c75-9975-4b86c80209f0", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-113/06-because", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "BECAUSE", :entity/source "Explicit encodings make exotype knowledge inspectable and comparable.", :xt/id "00abf421-55a2-4c75-9975-4b86c80209f0"} {:entity/id "00ae4605-2807-4dbb-894d-06c4597932f8", :entity/name "musn/psr-pur-real-actions", :entity/type :pattern/library, :entity/external-id "musn/psr-pur-real-actions", :entity/source "PSR/PUR Reflect Real Actions", :xt/id "00ae4605-2807-4dbb-894d-06c4597932f8"} {:entity/id "00b2bbd7-91a3-40d7-91bb-36a63604ffaa", :entity/name "iiching/exotype-136/conclusion", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "iiching/exotype-136/conclusion", :entity/source "Exotype 136 is encoded; program/params mapped from futon5; lift registry evidence recorded.", :xt/id "00b2bbd7-91a3-40d7-91bb-36a63604ffaa"} {:entity/id "00b9fb6b-732f-4f21-8de9-51b79cc7c5b0", :entity/name "iching/hexagram-34-dazhuang/because", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "iching/hexagram-34-dazhuang/because", :entity/source "Power is sustainable only when governed.", :xt/id "00b9fb6b-732f-4f21-8de9-51b79cc7c5b0"} {:entity/id "00ba1f15-f203-4652-8c98-e3640e6df1a5", :entity/name "repository-transition/job-argument/07-therefore", :entity/type :pattern/component, :entity/external-id "therefore", :entity/source "productive tensions rather than failures.\nMisalignment between identity and capability appears as", :xt/id "00ba1f15-f203-4652-8c98-e3640e6df1a5"} {:entity/id "00bab7bf-3c6a-4bd9-8e28-dd8cef5873c8", :entity/name "exotic/construction-discipline/because", :entity/type :pattern/clause, :entity/external-id "exotic/construction-discipline/because", :entity/source "Construction discipline provides runtime safety without per-operation overhead (validate once, trust thereafter). Property tests provide confidence in the constructors themselves. Test logs contribute to exotic scoring (regimes that pass more tests are healthier).", :xt/id "00bab7bf-3c6a-4bd9-8e28-dd8cef5873c8"} {:entity/id "00bd56af-30e9-48c7-ba3e-17a9ae3d13b7", :entity/name "sorry|devmap|futon4|P0|self-documenting-foundations", :entity/type :sorry, :entity/external-id "sorry|sorry|devmap|futon4|P0|self-documenting-foundations", :entity/source "stack-geometry-sorries", :entity/props {:sorry/next-steps ["Maintain synchronization as system evolves"], :sorry/however "Without self-documenting infrastructure, docs and code drift apart", :sorry/if "You want documentation and implementation to stay synchronized", :sorry/title "Prototype 0 — Self-Documenting Foundations", :sorry/evidence-operational ["spine.org provides master orchestration with tangling machinery (lines 19-103)" "dev/bootstrap.el is repeatable build harness for interactive + batch builds" "AGENTS.md is development manifesto describing Phase 1/2 strategy" "docs/reanimation-plan.org tracks M0-M6 milestones with checkbox progress" "test/arxana-bootstrap-test.el validates baseline harness (3 tests)" "arxana-tangled.el is generated single-source output (3752 lines) proving round-trip"], :sorry/pass-criteria ["Tangling produces consistent output" "Bootstrap harness runs without errors" "Documentation reflects current implementation"], :sorry/maturity "settled", :sorry/inhabited-ness "settled", :sorry/sigils ["🌽/久" "🙅/才"], :sorry/context "A key use case for futon4 is to align software documentation and code.", :sorry/scale "devmap", :sorry/source {:file "/home/joe/code/futon3/holes/futon4.devmap", :order 0}, :sorry/status "closed", :sorry/then "Make the system self-docu